  "body": "how does remix-ide could use the local compilier?\r\n\r\n**Situation: **Because of some reason, I visit the online solc compilier (https://solc-bin.ethereum.org/bin) is really slowly.\r\nEverytime I select a solidity version, more than hours to waiting the loading. So I wanted to use a local compilier with remix-ide.\r\n\r\n\r\n**What had I done:** \r\n   1. downloaded solc-bin from: https://github.com/ethereum/solc-bin.git\r\n   2. My remix-ide path is : /usr/local/lib/node_modules/remix-ide\r\n      and the downloaded solc-bin path is: /usr/local/lib/node_modules/remix-ide/solc-bin\r\n   3. I modified the remix-ide/build/app.js\r\n      3.1: modified from : var url = 'https://ethereum.github.io/solc-bin/bin/soljson-' + versionString + '.js';\r\n                     to: var url = 'http://localhost:8080/solc-bin/bin/list.json',\r\n                      I alse visited 'http://localhost:8080/solc-bin/bin/list.json', it was OK, the list.json returns OK.\r\n\r\n      3.2: modified from : baseurl: 'https://solc-bin.ethereum.org/bin'  \r\n                    to : baseurl: 'http://localhost:8080/solc-bin/bin'\r\n\r\n   4. restart remix-ide\r\n\r\n**Question:** it did not work for me. So i really want to know how does remix-ide could use the local compilier?",
